itemAv.scopeAndContentNote: This film shows the buildup of aircraft and supplies on Taiwan (Formosa), including visits by General Curtis LeMay, Chief of Staff, USAF, and Major General Thomas Moorman, Jr., Commander 13th Air Force, and pre-employment activities at George Air Force Base (AFB), California during the 1958 offshore islands crisis at Taiwan.
itemAv.shotList:
Reel 1 -- Scenes at Taoyuan ABA Taiwan include General (Gen.) Curtis E. LeMay boarding and alighting from a KC-135; USAF airmen alighting from a C-97; USAF personnel unloading F-104's from a 1705th Air Transport Group C-124; mattresses being unloaded from a C-130 and bedding supplies and Jeeps from a 1502nd Air Transport Wing C-130A; assembly and towing away of F-104's; a C-130A taxiing; an F-104 taxiing and taking off; and Chinese Nationalist civilians erecting a tent. 650' Total footage in reel.

Reel 2 -- Several scenes of Chinese Nationalist pilots scrambling; pilots boarding Chinese F-86F and aircraft taxiing; takeoff of a C-124; USAF personnel shaving and dressing in an unfinished tent; two US and two Chinese Nationalist pilots talking in front of Chinese F-86F aircraft; and shots of USAF F-86D inspection. 502' Total footage in reel.

Reel 3 -- Scenes at Taoyuan AB include a parked F-104 named EXCALIBUR with USAF pilot climbing into aircraft; collective and individual shots of three F-104's parked on hardstands; 83d FIS pilot alights from F-104 and talks to other pilots; scenes of an F-104 being towed and US airmen pushing another; US airmen eating at tables in an open tent; CU of 83d insignia; and shots of USAF mechanics pushing F-104 onto flight line, and pilot entering cockpit -- aircraft taxiing, taking off and flying over at low altitude.  Night scenes show USAF mechanics performing maintenance on F-104's. 820' Total footage in reel.

Reel 4 -- Scenes at Taoyuan AB include three F-104's taking off singly to the right; Chinese Nationalist F-86F's taking off two abreast; C-130 taxiing; F-104's taking off singly; F-104 taxiing up to a tow-bar as another taxis from hardstand onto flight line. Also included are scenes of a C-54 taxiing, Gen. Thomas S. Moorman, Jr., Commander 13th Air Force, alighting from aircraft; and being given a tour of the area by a USAF lieutenant colonel. Night scenes of USAF mechanics working on an F-104. 588' Total footage in reel. Reel 5 -- Scenes at Taoyuan AB include USAF personnel working on a building foundation; the tent area' with USAF personnel and Chinese civilians putting up tents; a Chinese Nationalist security guard on duty as a KC-135 takes off; 1705th Air Transport Group C-124 taxiing, parked, and CU of the squadron insignia; crated missile warheads, detonating fuses, unit supplies, and rocket ammunition. Also shows scenes of F-104's being unloaded from C-124, assembled, landing gears being checked, and an F-104 being towed by a jeep. 860' Total footage in reel.

Reel 6 -- Coverage of a tour to Shun-Shan Airfield, Taiwan by Gen. Curtis E. LeMay. Shows Gen. LeMay being greeted by Gen. Shu-Ming Wang, Chief of General Staff, Chinese Nationalist Ministry of Defense and Major General Shao Yang, Air Attache to the Chinese Embassy in Washington, D.C.; Gen. LeMay reviewing the honor guard; Major General Thomas S. Moorman, Jr., and Vice-Admiral Smoot touring the base with General LeMay; several Chinese Nationalist pilots being greeted by ground crewmen and other pilots after a mission in which they destroyed seven Communist Chinese MIG's; and General LeMay attending celebration in honor of the Chinese Nationalist pilots and congratulating them. 806' Total footage in reel.

Reel 7 -- F-101 TO FORM0SA. (printed on leader) Scenes include USAF pilots dressing, eating, and attending a briefing session; an airman sounding a scramble alarm; a sign: GEORGE AFB, HOME OF THE 831ST DIVISION; flight line scenes of F-101 being towed, an F-100 and a T-33 being parked; and individual shots of 11 RF-101 pilots in or near aircraft -- camera pans to parked RF-101's and RF-101's taking off, two abreast. 238' Total footage in reel.

itemAv.scopeAndContentNote:
This film documents the Taiwan alert when the Chinese Communist Government on the mainland threatened to invade the offshore islands of Quemoy and Natsu.  The film shows a U.S. Air Force (USAF) sentry on duty; a USAF airman as he climbed radar antennas to make adjustments; a USAF sergeant as he ate rations out of a tin can; an airman who was at alert on a telephone switchboard; Linkow Station on Taiwan with signs that read: "176TH USASA CO.", "253RD USASA DET. U.S. NAVSECGRUDET", "DET 1 6925TH RGM", and "The 6209TH ABRON"; and United States and Chinese nationalist flags that flew side-by-side. The film also shows maintenance men, including the Lockheed Company's famous "midget mechanic," as they worked on a Lockheed supersonic interceptor aircraft (F-104A) on a ramp; a pilot as he donned his gear and boarded a 
F-104A;  the F-104A as it took off; a Douglas Globemaster cargo aircraft (C-124D) parked on a ramp; a F-104A as it flew to the right then taxied with the parachute brake extended.

Reel 2: CU, buildings of Taipei: Capitol, Bank of Taiwan, Ministry of Transportation and Commerce, Legislature, Town Hall, Health Shrine (ints), and Botanical Gardens. HS, city streets and traffic as motorcycles, rickshaws and cars pass. Travel Shot, commercial district and marketplace. Int, tea factory as young children sift tea leaves. Reel 4: CU, Formosan girls sit around table during tea ceremony. Girls walk over bridge and through gardens. CU, Formosan girl. Express train travels RtoL; int, parlor car of train as passengers look over countryside. Travel shot, past railroad station and Formosan countryside. Animated map of train route from Taihoku to Taichou. VS, Taichou, city park, gardens, lakes, streams, fountains, Agricultural Inspection Center for fruit grown on island. Workmen dry rice. Water buffaloes wade in stream. Woven baskets and straw hats. CU, hands weaving straw hats. Railroad bridge as train proceeds southward. LS, railroad station. VS, lumber yard as huge logs are moved via overhead trolley onto conveyor belt, and into sawmill. Workmen stencil boards of cut lumber. Reel 5: Travel shot, territory of Formosa as train climbs mountainous area. Train passes railroad station of Sunkiko as people await and board train. Train arrives at Arisan. VS, Arisan including homes of families, schools, various scenic spots. VS, Tozan area. Lumberjack climbs huge mahogany tree, descends to ground. CU, bark of tree. VS, large pieces of lumber are moved across area by aerial trestle, wheels of machinery in operation. Large pieces of lumber are loaded onto bed of train fartransportation. Pan, mountain area. Seq, Group of campers awake in morning and look down upon cloud formations below them, then pack and set off across footbridge to further ascend mountain. VS, pineapple during stages of growth from sandbox to open field of huge pineapple bushes. CU, various fruits grown on experimental station grounds. CU, child's book. Formosan child reads from book. LS, Hokuho shrine. MS, monument in northern sector. Sugar cane fields as seen from fast moving train window. Railroad station of Tainan. City streets, shrine, park, harbor scenes and other historical sites of city of Tainan. CU, raft (camping). HS, salt fields. Workers extract salt from fields. organization.administrativeHistoryNote:
The American Institute in Taiwan (AIT) was the representative office of the United States in Taiwan. The establishment of diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China (PRC) in 1979 required acknowledgment of the One-China policy and termination of diplomatic relations with the Republic of China. However, the AIT assisted and protected U.S. interests in Taiwan and other areas in the ROC in a non-official manner.

AIT was a non-profit private corporation incorporated in the District of Columbia and founded in 1979 after U.S. established full diplomatic relations. Although AIT was a formally private institution, it was authorized by Section 6 of the Taiwan Relations Act (Publ. L. 96-8) approved April 10, 1979, to perform functions such as issuing visas for tourists and passports for US citizens. With the authorization of Taiwan Relations Act, the Department of State, through a non-official and private contract with AIT, provided AIT guidance and some funding in its operations. In practice the staff of the AIT consisted of largely of employees of the Department of State who are on leave from the Department.

itemAv.shotList: Documentation of EC-121H Air Defense Fighter Control operations showing aircraft taxiing, taking off, and in flight, flight crews during mission, at duty stations, relaxing in crew lounge, and aircraft maintenance. Also shows armed F-4's taxiing and taking off from Da Nang AB. Reel 1: SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7G-132. DA NANG AB. 2' MS of camouflaged F-4C's carrying Sparrows and Sidewinders and camouflaged F-4D carrying napalms, wing tanks, and gun pod SUU-16/A M61, 20mm gun taxiing past camera to right. 54' ELS's to LS of four F-4's taking off one after the other to the right. 79' EDITOR'S SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7G-149. DA NANG. 82' LS from under wing of C-123 as a camouflaged F-4C taxis out of revetment and past camera to right. 102' LS's of two camouflaged F-4C's carrying missiles taxiing to right and left. 132' LS's from under nose of F-4C as camouflaged F-4D taxis out from revetment area with tailaway shot -- F-4C with SUU-7A/A dispenser taxis into scene. 177' EDITOR'S SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-1701. 181' LS through EC-121H windscreen as aircraft flies over ships in harbor at Da Nang. 197' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X- (BLANK). 201' AMS of ocean -- EC-12lH engine in fg. 218' SLATE: ROLLS: R30C-7X-1790 AND 1791. TAIWAN. 223' Scenes of flight crews leaving two-story wooden barracks, putting their baggage into pickup truck, getting into Metro truck as seen through door opening, and both vehicles pulling away. 329' Travel shot of Metro truck arriving at EC-121 -- shows flight crew getting out of Metro truck and loading baggage into aircraft. 418' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-1792. 422' MS's including high angle from aircraft of flight crew boarding. 436' MS left FV of EC-12lH inboard engine starting, ground maintenance man giving engine start and taxi out signals, chocks being pulled, and aircrafft taxiing out. 499' LS of EC-121H taking off to left. 520' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-1793. TAIWAN. 523' Scenes of mechanics working on EC-12lH right outboard engine -- shows prop turning and crew chief in doorway of aircraft. 606' MCU & CU of ADC insignia on tail of EC-121H. 617' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-1794. 620' Scenes of mechanics changing spark plugs in EC-121H. 713' MS's of line crewman working at desk on flight line. 720' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-2596 (ON SLATE). TAN SON NHUT AB. 723' MS of Big Bye crew going down flight of steps. 728' MS & MLS left FV of EC-12lH engines starting -- shows aircraft taxiing out. 764' ELS to LS of EC-121H on takeoff run to left. 779' Total footage in reel. Reel 2: SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-2816. 1' MS of sweep on radar screen with CU of the operator's face (airman second class). 29' MS high angle looking over shoulder of two radar operators at consoles. 43' CU FV of face of radar operator. 52' MS FV & SV of plotters marking on transparent plotting board. 71' MS & CU of radio monitor at station. 89' MS of radar operator (Senior Director 1Lt Decarlo) as seen through plotting board. 97' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-2936.  TAN SON NHUT AB. 100' MS left SV of EC-121H engines starting. 106' MS RV of EC-121H taxiing out. 120' LS to MLS to MS of EC-121H in RTO to left and taxiing out left frame. 170' MLS of flight crew boarding BC-121H. 175' SLATE: ROLL: R30C-7X-2902. 178' MCU's zoom in to CU's and back of a first lieutenant and Maj Banks speaking individually -- shows Maj Banks getting up from his seat and walking up to cockpit. 353' EDITOR'S SLATE: ROLLS: R30C-7B-106 AND 107. 358' ALS's, AMLS's & AMS's of EC-121H in flight to right and left above clouds and camera aircraft passing under and over EC-121H. 545' Total footage in reel. Reel 3: SLATE: ROLL: 1. 4' AMS's of EC-121H engine and wingtip tank during flight. 29' AV's through EC-121 windscreen as aircraft makes pass over aircraft carrier ENTERPRISE. 68' AMS of EC-121H engine during flight. 75' AMCU's of copilot at station. 91' SLATE: ROLL: 2. 93' Scenes of scopes showing intensity of echo and sweep with blips on radarscopes. 153' AMS & AMCU of crew off station eating flight lunches. 181' AMS & AMCU's of flight engineer, pilot, and copilot at their stations. 224' AMS's of Capt Erickson reading and others writing letters and lying down relaxing. 251' AMS's of weather radar, radio, and radar operators at their stations -- shows the latter marking on face of scope. 398' Total footage in reel.

itemAv.shotList: Summary: Coverage of damage caused by 100 MPH winds of Typhoon Pamela which destroyed over 20,000 homes and killed 120 persons on the island. Reel 1: SLATE: WOODWORTH. AV's of Ilan, Taiwan, showing damaged huts and buildings and flooded rice paddies. 186' SLATE: WOODWORTH. 188' SLATE: MCCOLUM. Shows Chinese funeral procession in Suao, Taiwan moving through typhoon-ravaged town, citizens repairing damage and cleaning up. 372' SLATE:  MCCOLUM. Shows damage to buildings in Suao, bricks being cleaned, roof tile being laid and boy carrying girl on back. 560' SLATE:  MCCOLUM. Shows townspeople repairing houses; damaged pedi-cab, temple, and fishing boats. 742' Total footage in reel. Reel 2: 1' SLATE: MCCOLUM. Shows damaged buildings in Suao, downed telephone pole and damaged cement factory. 182' SLATE: MCCOLUM. Shows workers cleaning up and repairing damage at cement factory and children in damaged school room. 366' SLATE: MCCOLUM. Shows damaged cement factory, workers repairing roof and transporting materials, downed power limes and trees, damaged buildings, and children in damaged classroom. 545' Total footage in reel. Good (Basic: Orig neg)

itemAv.shotList: MLS, Maj Gen L L Doan, CG, US Armed Forces, Taiwan, breaks ground at future Nike sites at Yang Mei. Doan and his staff, consisting also of Nike team, walk around area. Col M Vaughn, Chief, DA Nike Team, chats with Danny Chang, CO of the new Nike Chinese Bn. In background, bulldozers start to work. HS & GSs in courtyard of the Sugar Bldg, Comm Center, Taiwan Base Command, as Chinese laborers start to unpack single side band equipment (radio). (Underexposed.) LS, jet planes consisting of FJ-4 Furys and Sky Rays at Ping Tung Airport. Two Marine pilots rush to planes, get into craft. Ground men assist them to put on their gear. MS, pilot in plane gives thumbs up sign. HS, two Sky Rays with their engine hoods up on the field. Two FJ-4 Fury jet planes take off in formation. Sky Ray in flight. Another plane lands back on field. Two mechanics work on Fury jet. CU, "Marines" on plane. CU, Sign: "Marine Fighter Squadron VMF-451" and insignia. Merchant Marine vessel Ocean Eva enters Kaohsiung Harbor. Three Chinese officers and two American Sgts board Ocean Eva. HS and deck shots as they look at one of the LCMs which are being turned over to the Chinese Nationalists. MS, group checks plans and specifications. HS, as Chinese laborers board the vessel; Guard checks their identification tags. HS, laborers remove hatch. Hatch covers are removed. Shot of the hold which is loaded with ammo. Ammo in a sling is unloaded. HS, laborers stack ammo boxes in hold. A laborer operates crane lift. Ammo is stacked on dolly. CU on case, "Cannon Ammo, etc." HS, laborers stacking ammo in ship's hold; the sling load is raised. A few static shots of laborers at LCMs on the Ocean Eva (poor).
